    <body>
        <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid/dist/mermaid.min.js"></script>
        <script>
            mermaid.initialize({ startOnLoad: true });
        </script>

        Here is one mermaid diagram:
        <div class="mermaid">
            graph LR 
            A[kittycat] --> B[netcat] 
            B --> C[catnip] 
            C --> D[response.http] & E[body] --> A
        </div>

        <p>kc (kittycat) pipes to nc (netcat) which pipes to cn (catnip).
        <ol>
            <li>netcat gets network request (e.g. HTTP GET)</li>
            <li>which is piped to catnip</li>
            <li>catnip attempts to (rudimentarily) process HTTP request</li>
            <li>and writes response.http and body files</li>
            <li>and signals kittycat</li>
            <li>kittycat awakes when nipped by catnip</li>
            <li>and cats files (as any good cat does)</li>
            <li>which are piped to netcat</li>
            <li>which responds over the network</li>
        </ol>
	<p>voila. the second-dumbest web server than netcat alone.
    </body>
</html>
